    "content": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "*Disclosure: Some links below are affiliate links. If you make a purchase, TonyCiencia may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.*",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I have spent more hours than I care to admit clicking through AI image generators. Some produce muddy results. Others lock the good models behind enterprise pricing. OpenArt AI hit differently from the first session — the outputs were sharp, the controls actually made sense, and the credit system felt fair.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you have been curious about diving into AI image creation or you are looking for a platform that handles everything from still images to short video clips, this guide walks you through the best ways to use OpenArt AI and tips that will level up your results fast.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l0",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://openartai.pxf.io/c/6249333/3106413/38572"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "**Start creating with OpenArt AI here**",
            "marks": [
              "l0"
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What Makes OpenArt AI Worth Your Attention",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "OpenArt AI is a web-based platform that gives you access to multiple AI models under one roof. We are talking about Stable Diffusion variants, FLUX, ControlNet workflows, and over 100 premium image, video, and audio models. Instead of juggling different apps or self-hosting models on your own machine, everything runs inside a clean browser workspace.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What I appreciate most is the layer of control. You can go from a simple text prompt to a fully styled image in seconds, or you can dig into ControlNet to guide poses, edges, and depth maps for precise compositions. That range — from beginner-friendly to granular — is rare.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The platform also supports consistent character creation, one-click story generation, and short video clips. So if you are building a brand with a mascot, writing a comic, or prototyping social content, OpenArt AI covers a lot of ground in one subscription.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Best Tips for Getting Stunning Results with OpenArt AI",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "1. Start with a Strong Prompt Structure",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A vague prompt like \"a warrior\" will give you generic output. Instead, structure your prompt with four layers:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Subject",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": A female samurai in crimson armor",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Setting",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": Standing on a cliff at golden hour",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Style",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": Cinematic lighting, Studio Ghibli influence",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Technical",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": ": 8K detail, shallow depth of field",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "OpenArt AI responds well to this kind of layered input because its models — especially FLUX and SDXL variants — are trained on detailed captioning. The more context you provide, the closer the first generation gets to your vision.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "2. Use ControlNet to Lock Down Composition",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This is where OpenArt AI separates itself from simpler tools. ControlNet lets you upload a reference sketch, a pose skeleton, or a depth map, and the AI generates an image that follows that structure.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Practical example: I uploaded a rough pencil sketch of a character pose, ran it through the OpenPose ControlNet module, and got a fully rendered character in the exact stance I wanted — on the first try. No more generating 40 images hoping one lands in the right pose.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "3. Leverage Consistent Characters for Branding",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/what-is-openart-ai"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "One of the newest features on ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "OpenArt AI",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " is consistent character creation. You train a small personalized model on a few reference images of your character, and then every future generation keeps that character recognizable across different scenes and outfits.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you are building a YouTube channel mascot, an illustrated book series, or even marketing visuals for a product, this feature saves enormous time. No more explaining to the AI what your character looks like every single prompt.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "4. Experiment with Parallel Generations",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Depending on your plan, OpenArt AI lets you run 8, 16, or more generations simultaneously. This is not just a speed perk — it is a creative strategy. Generate eight variations of the same prompt with slightly different seeds or style modifiers, then pick the winner. You will find that small tweaks in phrasing produce wildly different moods, and side-by-side comparison makes the best version obvious.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "5. Try One-Click Stories for Narrative Projects",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you have ever wanted to create a short visual story but felt overwhelmed by the workflow, OpenArt AI's One-Click Story feature handles the heavy lifting. You give it a premise, and it generates a sequence of illustrated panels with consistent characters and environments. It is a fast way to prototype a comic, a storyboard, or a social media story series.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://openartai.pxf.io/c/6249333/3106413/38572"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "**Unlock the full creative suite at OpenArt AI**",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
